pond with rock faces behind detector. Artemisia tridentata ssp. wyomingensis near detector.
cows present at recovery.  Waterhole w/rock face and old growth juniper behind detector; scattered juniper in vicinity of pond
mid cliff, overlooking slow moving portion of 20 Mile Crk; small rock face on opp. Side below mic. Level; learger rock face to north, scattered juniper; near ag land & beaver pond further down stream
low sage/juniper ecotone; ~250 m from Big Reservoir Stock pond, but large powerline above pond was too noisy to place detector at that site.

7/13/16 - Bats observed roosting under house siding of small house - 250+ counted. 2 species observed - one bat had visibly larger ears. Fewere bats roosting on larger house. Lots of mosquitos, other insects, and swallows swarming over lawn. 7/14/16 - Vau
lots of mosquitos; swallowtail butterfly; Swainson's thrush, Stellar's jay, pileated woodpecker, winter wren, Himalayan blackberry edge behind bat monitor
evidence of old forest fire. No water nearby.  Rocky hummocks covered with moss, vine maple, Huckleberry it. Berry, and bear grass. Lots of mosquitoes, bugs, flies, gnats, native bees.

Huckleberry (lots of berries!), Douglas spirea. Heard Swainson's thrush, common yellowthroat, willow flycatchers, white-crowned sparrow, S. jay. Lots of mosquitoes, flies, native bees. Bull elk tracks and fresh scat. Trout spp. in wetland/stream.

Mitigation site w/wapato, smartweed, monkey flower, Calex spp., tula spp. etc. Not a secure site! Equipment must be well hidden for the public and picked up early.  Host site to be developed and increased security.

Sparsely vegetated sand flats, primarily covered w/grasses and dry moss/lichen. Wetland behind site and across railroad tracks. Several ODA insect traps deployed in the immediate area. Secondary site down railroad tracks to bridge and wetland.

Site located at City Reservoir behind locked gate. Permission to access through Public Works Superintendent (Dan Foultier, 503-556-7301) Reservoir recently drained and sediment removed. Dam made of wood w/sloping face. Friends of Fox Crk installed bat box

Approximately 1.26 miles from 119485SW1, 1 snag near wetland border, mosquitos and dragon flies present culvert under Road creates some noise, winds created additional noise, small wetland could be accessd near snag and away from culvert.
